## Review Summary: Issue #48 — Daily Updates Component Migration

**Result: PASSED**

### Acceptance Criteria

| Criterion | Status |
|---|---|
| Feed cards use `@repo/ui` Card | **PASS** — Card, CardHeader, CardContent, CardFooter |
| Profile badges use `@repo/ui` Badge/Avatar | **PASS** — Avatar/AvatarFallback for source icons, Badge for priority & category |
| Category filters use shared components | **PARTIAL** — Time range tabs migrated to Tabs/TabsTrigger; two `<select>` dropdowns remain raw HTML |
| All buttons use `@repo/ui` Button | **PASS** — Reactions, load more, links, CTA all use Button |
| `pnpm build` passes | **PASS** |

### Findings

- **WARNING**: The app filter and category filter dropdowns (`feed-app.tsx:322-354`) still use raw `<select>` elements. `@repo/ui` doesn't export a Select component, so there's no direct replacement available. PillList exists but would change the UX from dropdown to pill selection. This is a reasonable trade-off.

- **INFO**: The migration is otherwise thorough — Input, EmptyState, Tabs, and all Button/Card/Badge/Avatar usages are clean and well-structured. The about page was also properly migrated.